$ Python - sqlite3: Select single row (fetchone)

The `fetchone` method of the → development/languages/Python/PEP/0249#py-sqlite-cursor-obj[cursor] object returns one record as a → development/languages/Python/types/tuple.

{ Inserting a record and getting its rowid

  The following simple example inserts a record into a table with a `returning rowid` clause and used `fetchone()` to return the inserted record's → development/databases/SQLite/tables/rowid.
  -
  Because we're interested in the first (and only) element of the returned tuple, we subscript it: `fetchone()[0]`.

